basic Mandatory Linux/Unix Commands for QA's / SDET's for any Project where Shell Scripting is involved :- 

Navigating to the Directories :- 

▪️cd <directory> ➡️ Change directory.
▪️ls ➡️ List files and directories.
▪️ls -l ➡️ List files with details.
▪️cd .. ➡️ Move to parent directory 
▪️pwd ➡️ Print working directory.

File Operations :- 

▪️touch <filename> ➡️ Create an empty file.
▪️cp <source> <destination> ➡️ Copy files.
▪️mv <source> <destination> ➡️ Move or rename files.
▪️rm <filename> ➡️ Remove files.
▪️rm -r <directory> ➡️ Remove directory and its contents.

Viewing and Editing Files :- 

▪️cat <filename> ➡️ Display file contents.
▪️less <filename> ➡️ View file content page by page.
▪️nano <filename> ➡️ Simple text editor.
▪️vim <filename> ➡️ Advanced text editor.

Searching and Processing Text :- 

▪️grep <pattern> <filename> ➡️ Search for a pattern in a file.
▪️find <directory> -name <pattern> ➡️ Find files by name.
▪️awk '{print $1}' <filename> ➡️ Print the first column of a file.

Permissions and Ownership :- 

▪️chmod <permissions> <filename> ➡️ Change file permissions.
▪️chown <user>:<group> <filename> ➡️ Change file owner and group.

System Information :- 

▪️uname -a ➡️ Display system information.
▪️df -h ➡️ Display disk space usage.
▪️top ➡️ Display running processes.

Networking :- 

▪️ping <hostname> ➡️ Check network connectivity.
▪️ifconfig ➡️ Display network configuration

Process Management :- 

▪️ps ➡️ Display running processes.
▪️kill <PID> ➡️ Terminate a process.
▪️killall <process> ➡️ Terminate all processes with the name.

Other :- 
▪️echo "text" ➡️ Printing text to console.

